<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="S" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Suitor" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Suitor</orth> (pronounced like <emph>shooter</emph> in <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.110" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 110</bibl>) 1) a petitioner: <bibl n="shak. lll 2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.151" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 151</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.1.138" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 1, 138</bibl> <emph>(I will not be your s.,</emph> i. e. submissive to you). <bibl n="shak. 3h6 3.1.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C III, 1, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.64" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.2.9" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 2, 9</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 61</bibl> <cit><quote>(they say poor --s have strong breaths).</quote> <bibl n="shak. tit 1.44" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 44</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.3.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 3, 12</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.4.15" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.4.15" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 4, 15</bibl> <bibl n="shak. jc 3.1.227" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 227</bibl> <cit><quote>(am moreover s. that I may produce his body).</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 3.1.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 1, 51</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.42" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 42</bibl>. With <emph>to</emph>: <cit><quote>I am a woeful s. to your honour,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 2.2.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. II, 2, 27</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>she hath been a s. to me for her brother,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 5.34.27" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 34</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. cor 5.3.78" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. V, 3, 78</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 3.5.7" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. III, 5, 7</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ant 2.1.4" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 1, 4</bibl>.<lb />2) one who follows women: <cit><quote>no heretics burned, but wenches' --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 3.2.84" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 2, 84</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>she that could . . . see --s following and not look behind,</quote> <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.158" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 158</bibl></cit>.
<lb />3) a wooer, a lover: <bibl n="shak. ven 6" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tgv 2.1.143" default="NO" valid="yes">Gent. II, 1, 143</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.130" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 130</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 4.1.110" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 1, 110</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.169" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.2.38" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 38</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ayl 3.2.438" default="NO" valid="yes">As III, 2, 438</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.1.189" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 1, 189</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.243" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 243</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.243" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 243</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.243" default="NO" valid="yes">I, 2, 243</bibl> <bibl n="shak. shr 2.8.243" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 8</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. shr 2.8.243" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 8</bibl> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.3.109" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 3, 109</bibl>. With <emph>to</emph>: <cit><quote>--s to her,</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.122" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 2, 122</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>are you a s. to the maid?</quote> <bibl n="shak. shr 1.2.122" default="NO" valid="yes">Shr. I, 2, 122</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. shr 2.91.122" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.6.2" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 6, 2</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>